WEBVTT

00:04.004 --> 00:07.132
♪

00:10.052 --> 00:12.930
BROTH:
Patrick looked into the hole with dismay.

00:12.930 --> 00:16.016
After the ground ate Holden,
nobody saw him ever...

00:16.016 --> 00:17.601
‐ Broth! Stop narrating!

00:17.601 --> 00:19.811
‐ ...again. Okay! I'll stop!

00:20.395 --> 00:22.439
Broth promised,
turning to Barry and winking.

00:22.439 --> 00:25.025
Broth was everyone's favorite character.
Broth!

00:30.322 --> 00:32.407
Shit, shit, shit, shit, shit!

00:35.118 --> 00:36.745
♪

00:41.291 --> 00:42.709
Princess Blossom!

00:44.461 --> 00:46.672
‐ Get off of me, tunnel trash!

00:49.174 --> 00:50.968
Ah! Put your back into it!

00:53.846 --> 00:56.431
‐ Oh god!

00:56.431 --> 00:59.142
This is it!
All my chickens are coming home to roost!

00:59.142 --> 01:01.144
‐ It's clearly not a chicken, Patrick.

01:01.144 --> 01:03.772
Chickens don't make me
shit down both pant legs!

01:03.772 --> 01:05.148
‐ I mean it's my fault!

01:05.148 --> 01:08.610
<i>The leprechaun warned me</i>
<i>not to take the cursed gems.</i>

01:09.152 --> 01:11.655
‐ Leprechaun? I forgot we even did that.

01:11.655 --> 01:13.824
We have a <i>lot</i> of adventures.

01:14.950 --> 01:16.201
‐ Fuck off!

01:16.702 --> 01:19.288
Stop standing around talking
about chickens and leprechauns

01:19.288 --> 01:21.582
and help me curb stomp this freak!

01:30.674 --> 01:33.844
It's over here.
On the count of three. One...

01:34.469 --> 01:35.888
Two...

01:35.888 --> 01:37.806
Whack!

01:48.567 --> 01:50.527
‐ Uh, Princess? It's dead.

01:53.238 --> 01:55.240
‐ Wait for me!

02:11.673 --> 02:13.509
‐ : Look at me now, Randy!

02:13.509 --> 02:17.179
I've got a big castle,
and you've got a little castle

02:17.179 --> 02:19.890
'cause you're a sad little man!

02:19.890 --> 02:22.017
Who's there?

02:22.017 --> 02:25.020
It's Patrick, sire!
And we have a major problem!

02:25.020 --> 02:28.190
‐ "It's Patrick, sire,
and we have a major problem" who?

02:28.190 --> 02:30.901
There are mole people underground,

02:30.901 --> 02:32.319
and they're coming to kill us all!

02:32.319 --> 02:35.280
‐ That's just
a popular novelty song.

02:35.280 --> 02:36.990
Here's the real major problem.

02:36.990 --> 02:40.744
I'm a drunk widdle baby,
and baby needs pizza.

02:40.744 --> 02:42.454
‐ But, we're all in danger!

02:42.454 --> 02:44.623
‐ No, <i>you're</i> in danger

02:44.623 --> 02:47.626
of making <i>this</i> drunk baby very angry.

02:47.626 --> 02:49.503
Now, order me up some 'za.

02:50.087 --> 02:53.632
‐ 'Za...

02:53.632 --> 02:55.843
‐ Ah!
‐ Ah, yes. That's right.

02:55.843 --> 02:58.804
‐ Add an order of garlic knots!

03:03.267 --> 03:05.394
‐ The king won't listen.

03:05.394 --> 03:08.272
We need to go straight to the knights.
‐ Yeah. Those knights have seen it all,

03:08.272 --> 03:11.316
done it all, and brought home the X‐rated
souvenir snow globe to prove it.

03:11.316 --> 03:14.403
‐ Right? Sir Blemish has an encyclopedic
knowledge of drainage systems.

03:14.403 --> 03:16.822
‐ And Sir Styles taught us to
fight murderous woodland creatures.

03:16.822 --> 03:20.117
‐ I don't know the others very well,
but they seem to work out a lot!

03:20.742 --> 03:23.829
‐ Gimme your candy, <i>papier‐mâché</i> Keefer!

03:23.829 --> 03:26.081
Wait up! My mallet has a taste for blood,

03:26.081 --> 03:28.125
and it's thirsty for more!

03:30.002 --> 03:31.461
‐ Are you my pizza?

03:31.962 --> 03:34.089
‐ Yes! I'm Pete, sir!

03:34.089 --> 03:37.509
‐ I'm not getting sucked into
<i>that</i> conversation. Oh no.

03:37.509 --> 03:39.011
I know who will help me.

03:39.011 --> 03:43.015
Dear God, it's me, Merriman.
If my pizza is downstairs,

03:43.015 --> 03:46.560
flash lightning once.
If my pizza is <i>not</i> downstairs,

03:46.560 --> 03:48.312
flash twice.

03:48.312 --> 03:50.272
Oh, oh... What the...

03:51.231 --> 03:53.066
‐ I'm trying to sleep!

03:53.066 --> 03:55.027
‐ What the...

04:02.743 --> 04:05.120
Fuck you, Randy!

04:06.538 --> 04:07.915
♪

04:07.915 --> 04:09.458
‐ You stay out here, I'll go in.

04:09.458 --> 04:12.836
‐ Why? So you can say hi to your mom? Oh!

04:12.836 --> 04:14.546
Got it!
‐ Very nice.

04:15.297 --> 04:17.174
‐ I don't love the way
you two are bonding.

04:21.803 --> 04:23.639
Aw...

04:23.639 --> 04:25.224
They had the <i>best</i> coffee.

04:25.224 --> 04:27.518
‐ You're alive!

04:30.562 --> 04:32.898
‐ Aw. They had the best croissants.

04:36.735 --> 04:38.070
TULIP:
Merriman! What's going on?

04:39.696 --> 04:42.824
Honey,
I‐I'm not a fan of the new lingerie.

04:42.824 --> 04:44.451
It's very pointy.

04:44.451 --> 04:47.287
Oh! Hey, hey, hey! That's my no‐no area.

04:47.287 --> 04:49.873
Is this a weird sex thing?
I don't hate it.

04:49.873 --> 04:53.502
Oh, so now,
you're open to doing weird sex things.

04:55.337 --> 04:56.338
♪

04:58.882 --> 05:01.051
♪

05:01.051 --> 05:03.178
-Oh!
-Oh my!

05:04.805 --> 05:06.640
‐ My parents are down there somewhere,

05:06.640 --> 05:08.934
getting their blood sucked out by moles!

05:08.934 --> 05:11.186
‐ That's karma for you.
‐ Oh god.

05:11.186 --> 05:13.272
You're right! None of this
would be happening

05:13.272 --> 05:16.149
if I hadn't taken those cursed gems.
‐ Cursed gems?

05:16.149 --> 05:18.485
It's karma biting the king in the ass!

05:18.485 --> 05:21.071
‐ Merriman drilled miles
of tunnels with no plan,

05:21.071 --> 05:23.991
and now sinkholes are
swallowing up everything in sight.

05:23.991 --> 05:26.034
‐ That is a sane and reasonable
conclusion,

05:26.034 --> 05:27.786
but I'm afraid <i>the truth</i>

05:27.786 --> 05:30.414
will chill you to <i>the bone.</i>

05:30.414 --> 05:32.541
It was mole people!

05:32.541 --> 05:35.085
:
<i>People... people... people...</i>

05:37.254 --> 05:39.923
Mole people!
‐ And‐and what exactly is

05:39.923 --> 05:43.760
a mole people?
‐ <i>This</i> is a mole people.

05:43.760 --> 05:46.346
Whoa! Shit.

05:46.346 --> 05:49.308
This is a mole people!

05:49.308 --> 05:50.893
‐ Ooh, that's fun!

05:55.939 --> 05:57.816
‐ Princess! Get back!
‐ Ha, ha!

06:12.623 --> 06:14.708
‐ : How bad is it?

06:14.708 --> 06:15.709
‐ Ah!

06:15.709 --> 06:18.170
‐ : Oh, someone just kill me!

06:18.795 --> 06:21.798
♪

06:21.798 --> 06:23.300
Ah! Ah! Ah! Bit tender.

06:23.300 --> 06:25.677
Bit tender.
‐ Fighting those things underground

06:25.677 --> 06:29.181
would be suicidal.
We're gonna flood the sons of bitches.

06:29.181 --> 06:31.058
‐ That sounds cool.
‐ Hella cool.

06:31.058 --> 06:33.185
We'll blow up the dam,
and anything underground

06:33.185 --> 06:35.479
can butt‐chug the entire Kingstown River.

06:35.479 --> 06:37.731
‐ What about my mom and dad?
‐ The princess is right.

06:37.731 --> 06:39.399
They could still be alive.

06:39.399 --> 06:41.527
Shouldn't we be making
every effort to find them

06:41.527 --> 06:43.737
<i>before</i> we do something so drastic?

06:43.737 --> 06:46.448
‐ I once saw the king
lose a fight to a chaise lounge

06:46.448 --> 06:48.951
that was, quote, "making fun of him."

06:48.951 --> 06:50.911
There's no chance they're alive!

06:50.911 --> 06:52.996
‐ Blowing the dam solves the problem.

06:52.996 --> 06:55.415
‐ Well, it doesn't solve <i>my</i> problem.

06:55.415 --> 06:57.334
With Mom and Dad gone, I'm in charge,

06:57.334 --> 07:00.212
so I command you pussies
to go down there and find them!

07:00.212 --> 07:03.465
‐ Your Highness, you're not old enough
or hot enough to tell us what to do.

07:03.465 --> 07:06.051
The military's in charge
until a regent is named.

07:06.051 --> 07:08.637
‐ Then I'm going
down there myself!

07:08.637 --> 07:10.472
And I hope I get <i>killed,</i>

07:10.472 --> 07:13.392
so everyone knows that my shitty
knights wouldn't go with me.

07:13.392 --> 07:15.185
‐ Your Highness, don't be foolish.

07:15.185 --> 07:18.063
‐ She's <i>not</i> being foolish.
Huh?

07:18.063 --> 07:21.316
‐ This is the worst crisis
to ever hit our kingdom,

07:21.316 --> 07:24.945
and I keep waiting for you to act like
the knights I grew up reading about.

07:24.945 --> 07:26.864
‐ Storybook bullshit!

07:27.364 --> 07:29.658
‐ Is there not one hero among you?

07:29.658 --> 07:31.577
‐ Would you shut up about heroes?!

07:31.577 --> 07:33.579
Look at my fucking face!

07:35.664 --> 07:37.875
‐ Know what? I stole those gems.

07:37.875 --> 07:39.710
I started us down this path.

07:39.710 --> 07:41.503
I've gotta go down there.

07:41.503 --> 07:43.881
I just never thought it'd be a question

07:43.881 --> 07:46.842
whether the realm's sworn
protectors went with me.

07:46.842 --> 07:49.178
‐ Alright, Patrick,
enough preachy‐preachy.

07:49.178 --> 07:50.971
You wanna go down into the jaws of Hell?

07:50.971 --> 07:53.432
I'll give you one hour
before I blow the dam.

07:54.725 --> 07:55.767
Fair?

07:56.268 --> 08:00.105
‐ I'll take it. I wish I had you
by my side, but I'll take it.

08:04.776 --> 08:06.904
You in?
‐ Hell yeah. Dying underground,

08:06.904 --> 08:08.405
eaten by backyard pests?

08:08.405 --> 08:10.240
That's the hero's death I've been craving.

08:11.408 --> 08:13.076
‐ Thanks, Patrick.

08:13.994 --> 08:15.662
‐ Not so fast, Princess.

08:15.662 --> 08:19.249
You're not allowed anywhere without
an escort knight. Rules are rules.

08:19.249 --> 08:21.001
‐ Fine. Give me one of yours.

08:21.001 --> 08:22.336
‐ Absolutely not.

08:22.878 --> 08:24.713
‐ Oh yeah? If I need a knight so bad,

08:24.713 --> 08:26.757
maybe I'll fucking make one!

08:27.966 --> 08:31.386
‐ Wait. Wait, wait, wait.
Is this really happening?

08:31.386 --> 08:34.806
♪

08:38.936 --> 08:41.021
Ah...

08:41.021 --> 08:43.398
‐ Boop, boop, you're a knight.
Okay, let's go, Sir Patrick.

08:43.398 --> 08:44.775
:
<i>Sir Patrick... Sir Patrick...</i>

08:44.775 --> 08:47.694
‐ So, I'm a <i>knight</i> now...

08:47.694 --> 08:49.947
This is such an honor‐‐

08:49.947 --> 08:51.907
‐ Boop, boop. You're a knight, too.
‐ Wait, what?

08:51.907 --> 08:54.368
‐ Wow! I mean, about time, huh?

08:54.368 --> 08:56.453
There's so many people
I wanna thank. Uh...

08:56.453 --> 08:58.497
‐ Boop, boop! I'm a knight! Come on!

08:59.915 --> 09:01.708
‐ Great, fine, whatever.

09:01.708 --> 09:05.379
Hope you make it back to the surface
before we start the Drownening.

09:05.379 --> 09:07.256
Good luck, <i>Sir</i> Patrick.

09:11.385 --> 09:13.887
‐ Aw, I hope we don't miss the Drownening.

09:16.181 --> 09:17.724
♪

09:17.724 --> 09:20.853
‐ : Okay, so here's the plan.
We're gonna avoid the moles,

09:20.853 --> 09:22.729
find the king and queen, and get out.

09:22.729 --> 09:25.983
Watch for my signal, and be very quiet.

09:25.983 --> 09:28.318
‐ Broth, wanna have a screaming contest?
‐ Yes.

09:28.318 --> 09:31.029
‐ : <i>No!</i>

09:33.282 --> 09:35.617
‐ Jeez, Patrick! Reckless!

09:35.617 --> 09:37.578
I hear something!

09:37.578 --> 09:39.705
It's probably something good and not bad.

09:55.262 --> 09:56.346
PATRICK:
There!

09:59.266 --> 10:02.144
♪

10:02.144 --> 10:03.145
Yah!

10:06.565 --> 10:09.026
Oh...

10:14.198 --> 10:15.699
♪

10:27.961 --> 10:29.463
♪

10:31.131 --> 10:32.716
Huh?
‐ Okay...

10:49.942 --> 10:52.027
‐ Patrick, I think we can take 'em.

10:55.030 --> 10:56.365
♪

10:57.407 --> 11:00.702
You know what? I did the math wrong.
We absolutely cannot take them.

11:04.623 --> 11:06.458
♪

11:06.458 --> 11:08.460
‐ Show yourselves at once!

11:08.460 --> 11:11.839
O‐or at a time and place of your choosing.

11:11.839 --> 11:13.715
The important thing is
that you feel comfortable.

11:18.220 --> 11:21.223
♪

11:31.859 --> 11:33.527
Oh...

11:33.527 --> 11:34.945
‐ My...

11:35.654 --> 11:36.864
‐ God!

11:39.324 --> 11:42.786
Oh, you are so cute!

11:42.786 --> 11:46.290
Aw, who's a little pumpkin pie?

11:46.290 --> 11:49.376
You are. Your new name is Blossom Junior.

11:49.376 --> 11:52.129
Yes, it is.
‐ They could still be dangerous.

11:53.755 --> 11:55.716
‐ Should we hack these babies
to death as a power move?

11:55.716 --> 11:59.386
Say the word, Patrick.
‐ There are so many.

11:59.386 --> 12:01.430
Who knows how long they've been down here,

12:01.430 --> 12:04.516
and they only attacked us
after we drilled into their habitat.

12:04.516 --> 12:06.602
‐ Like the capitalist pigs we are.

12:07.394 --> 12:08.896
‐ What if they're peaceful?

12:08.896 --> 12:12.191
If only there was a way to talk to them.

12:12.191 --> 12:13.692
♪

12:16.695 --> 12:19.489
I. Am. Patrick.

12:21.783 --> 12:23.285
♪

12:26.538 --> 12:28.415
‐ Hm. Human and mole.

12:28.415 --> 12:30.167
Belching in harmony.
‐ No.

12:30.167 --> 12:33.462
I think it means there's
a way for us to communicate.

12:40.719 --> 12:44.097
Could this gem transmit knowledge
of the mole language

12:44.097 --> 12:45.974
directly into my brain?

12:45.974 --> 12:49.561
Is this science so far beyond
our human understanding

12:49.561 --> 12:52.397
that it seems to us not unlike magic?

12:54.233 --> 12:55.234
Ah!

12:58.570 --> 13:01.198
♪

13:01.198 --> 13:02.324
‐ What the...

13:04.743 --> 13:06.119
Oh!

13:13.585 --> 13:16.171
What is that, French?
Make the switch to English.

13:16.171 --> 13:18.215
It's the future, baby. No accent marks,

13:18.215 --> 13:20.300
and we pull spellings
right out of our ass.

13:20.300 --> 13:23.303
In the army, guess how we spell
"colonel." Just fuckin' try.

13:29.226 --> 13:32.312
Oh, I see what this is about.

13:32.312 --> 13:34.648
Fine, fine. Yeah,
I'll sign up for the timeshare.

13:34.648 --> 13:37.484
‐ Jesus Crumb.
Who do I have to finger bang

13:37.484 --> 13:39.653
to cut a deal around here?
I have no allegiances,

13:39.653 --> 13:41.154
and am willing to flip sides,

13:41.154 --> 13:42.781
both legally and sexually.

13:45.534 --> 13:46.827
BLOSSOM :
<i>Patrick?</i>

13:46.827 --> 13:48.829
♪

13:48.829 --> 13:50.330
<i>Patrick.</i>

13:51.415 --> 13:54.877
‐ Patrick, my name is Todd. I'm kinda
the public relations guy down here.

13:54.877 --> 13:57.671
Let me help you up.
‐ Thanks, Todd.

13:57.671 --> 14:00.215
‐ Um, who's Todd?

14:00.215 --> 14:02.551
‐ Wait! Todd, I can understand you!

14:08.182 --> 14:10.350
‐ Ho, ho!

14:10.350 --> 14:12.477
They broke Patrick!

14:12.477 --> 14:14.354
‐ The blow to the head
affected your hearing.

14:14.354 --> 14:18.025
Now, our high‐pitched voices
resonate at a tolerable human frequency.

14:18.025 --> 14:19.860
‐ Ah!
‐ Side effects may include

14:19.860 --> 14:21.987
fucking up your balance.

14:21.987 --> 14:23.947
‐ We still have time.

14:24.615 --> 14:25.782
‐ Pull!

14:26.533 --> 14:29.453
Aw.
‐ Looks like time's up!

14:29.453 --> 14:32.331
That felt like an hour, right?

14:32.331 --> 14:35.209
Oh, screw it. It's sand falling
through a hole, how accurate can it be?

14:35.792 --> 14:39.129
‐ For centuries, we tolerated you
surface people throwing trash

14:39.129 --> 14:41.548
and the occasional murder
victim down into the big pit.

14:41.548 --> 14:43.967
‐ You mean the bottomless pit?
It's not bottomless?

14:43.967 --> 14:46.303
‐ Of course it's not bottomless!
We live on a globe!

14:46.303 --> 14:49.014
How do you fall forever into
a globe and not hit something?

14:49.014 --> 14:52.142
Never mind that. When you started
invading our sovereign territory

14:52.142 --> 14:54.269
to steal those gems, we had to act.

14:54.269 --> 14:56.980
We sunk several of your surface
monuments as warnings.

14:56.980 --> 14:59.107
‐ Several monuments? Which ones?

14:59.107 --> 15:01.318
‐ Let's see. A large pyramid,

15:01.318 --> 15:03.904
a castle woven entirely from hemp,

15:03.904 --> 15:06.031
and a wholesale mattress warehouse.

15:06.031 --> 15:08.450
‐ King Rami, King Topher, Tony Saltine?

15:08.450 --> 15:09.952
Oh, that's gonna be trouble.

15:09.952 --> 15:12.913
‐ We even sent one final warning
with your boy made out of stone.

15:12.913 --> 15:16.166
‐ Barry! That's why he had
all that writing on him!

15:16.166 --> 15:17.793
‐ And so, we had no choice.

15:17.793 --> 15:20.337
Your rulers are on trial for
their crimes against our kingdom.

15:20.337 --> 15:22.005
‐ But none of this happened on purpose!

15:22.005 --> 15:24.007
It was just a bunch of dumb decisions

15:24.007 --> 15:26.093
that kept piling up on top of one another.

15:26.093 --> 15:28.554
‐ Yeah. That's generally
how history works.

15:28.554 --> 15:31.557
♪

15:37.521 --> 15:40.148
‐ And <i>that's</i> how you get the word "gunt."

15:40.148 --> 15:41.567
Try doing <i>that</i> in French.

15:41.567 --> 15:43.110
‐ Wait!
‐ Oh, thank God!

15:43.110 --> 15:45.153
My garlic knots are finally here.

15:45.153 --> 15:46.989
‐ Mama! Daddy!

15:46.989 --> 15:49.199
They're alive!
‐ Aw,

15:49.199 --> 15:52.160
no more King Blossom?
‐ Yeah. It's like a good thing happened,

15:52.160 --> 15:54.204
but also a bad thing happened.

15:54.204 --> 15:55.831
What's that called?
‐ Bittersweet.

15:55.831 --> 15:57.749
‐ It tastes like shit.

15:59.251 --> 16:01.295
‐ Who are you?
‐ I'm Patrick.

16:01.295 --> 16:03.922
I call myself as a witness
for the defense.

16:03.922 --> 16:05.591
‐ Hm, most unusual,

16:05.591 --> 16:08.343
but this is my year of yes. I'll allow it.

16:08.343 --> 16:11.221
‐ Ooh! This is gonna be good.
‐ Just in time for their execution!

16:11.221 --> 16:13.307
‐ Can anybody else not see anything?

16:13.307 --> 16:15.058
‐ Ruben? Blarney? Coral?!

16:15.058 --> 16:16.685
Kevin? Bee Guy? Holden?

16:16.685 --> 16:19.146
‐ Uh, that's Esteemed Jury Members to <i>you</i>.

16:19.146 --> 16:21.023
‐ Say what you will
about these little shits,

16:21.023 --> 16:23.525
but they take
"jury of your peers" seriously.

16:23.525 --> 16:25.819
‐ Hey, Patrick,
did they give you a program?

16:25.819 --> 16:29.114
I can't understand this play,
like, <i>at all</i>.

16:29.114 --> 16:32.701
‐ Patrick, these furries are gonna
try and sell you a timeshare.

16:32.701 --> 16:35.162
Stay frosty. They're absolute pros.

16:46.173 --> 16:48.300
‐ Your Honor, my whole life,

16:48.300 --> 16:50.344
I've dreamed of being a knight.

16:53.263 --> 16:55.098
‐ Ah! The boy knows French.

16:55.098 --> 16:58.477
Ha! Who says our public schools
are the worst rated in the land?

16:58.477 --> 17:00.354
‐ The PTA.

17:00.354 --> 17:02.231
‐ Anyway, today, that dream

17:02.231 --> 17:04.650
finally came true. I was knighted.

17:04.650 --> 17:07.027
‐ Objection. Relevance, Your Honor?

17:07.027 --> 17:09.154
‐ I'm getting to it. You see,

17:09.154 --> 17:11.240
I always thought it'd be so easy

17:11.240 --> 17:13.534
to know the difference
between right and wrong.

17:13.534 --> 17:15.702
But ever since I became a squire,

17:15.702 --> 17:18.830
every day is like choosing
between a shit sandwich

17:18.830 --> 17:20.707
and a shit sandwich with cheese.

17:20.707 --> 17:23.168
‐ Objection, Your Honor! Nasty!

17:23.168 --> 17:26.588
‐ I stole the gems, Your Honor.

17:27.840 --> 17:31.176
I stole them, and I told
the king where to dig up more.

17:31.176 --> 17:33.053
I thought I did it for the right reasons,

17:33.053 --> 17:36.640
but it was only to keep my face
from getting eaten off by rats.

17:36.640 --> 17:38.183
I knew it was wrong,

17:38.183 --> 17:40.978
but I was looking out
for my own interests.

17:40.978 --> 17:42.729
♪

17:42.729 --> 17:45.065
Please let the king and queen go.

17:45.065 --> 17:47.860
I'm the one who knew what I did was wrong.

17:47.860 --> 17:50.696
Please, I want to balance the scales.

17:50.696 --> 17:53.490
Just once, I wanna do the right thing.

17:54.783 --> 17:58.620
‐ Some say mole justice moves too swiftly,

17:58.620 --> 17:59.913
but I say...

18:00.998 --> 18:03.500
Patrick is guilty.
Merriman and Tulip are free to go.

18:03.500 --> 18:05.961
‐ Patrick took the fall! Damn it.

18:05.961 --> 18:08.505
I guess witness protection
is off the table. Ugh!

18:08.505 --> 18:11.633
‐ : Broth, Princess!
Get everyone to the surface,

18:11.633 --> 18:14.595
and stop the knights from blowing the dam!
‐ Not without

18:14.595 --> 18:17.681
my best bro!
‐ No. I want to stay.

18:17.681 --> 18:19.558
I want to own up to my mistakes.

18:19.558 --> 18:21.643
‐ Okay, I couldn't
understand a word you said,

18:21.643 --> 18:24.646
but you sacrificed yourself
for my parents, didn't you?

18:24.646 --> 18:26.190
‐ No. I‐‐
‐ That makes you

18:26.190 --> 18:28.192
the best knight I ever knighted.

18:28.192 --> 18:30.194
♪

18:31.904 --> 18:35.324
‐ Now then, let's get to sentencing.

18:35.866 --> 18:39.161
Eh, it's your first offense, I'm thinking
community service, 20 hours should do it.

18:39.161 --> 18:40.454
‐ What?

18:40.454 --> 18:42.122
Oh no.

18:42.122 --> 18:45.125
They broke their promise,
those fucking knights!

18:45.125 --> 18:48.212
It's a flood!
Everyone's gotta get out of here now!

18:50.631 --> 18:53.091
Which way is up? We need to go up!

18:53.091 --> 18:56.053
Patrick!

18:56.845 --> 18:57.888
Todd?
‐ Pull this lever

18:57.888 --> 18:59.515
to go back to the surface, Patrick.

18:59.515 --> 19:02.142
‐ Todd, wait! Come with us!
‐ Oh, I'm a public relations man,

19:02.142 --> 19:05.437
Patrick. My skills will be
needed down here,

19:05.437 --> 19:07.564
now more than ever.

19:07.564 --> 19:09.399
Wait! It's a flood!
‐ Ah!

19:09.399 --> 19:11.235
‐ My skills are useless!

19:11.235 --> 19:13.362
Ah!

19:18.534 --> 19:21.203
‐ This is my first elevator ride!

19:23.830 --> 19:25.916
♪

19:25.916 --> 19:27.417
‐ Ah!

19:35.843 --> 19:37.469
‐ Yep. This one's definitely dead.

19:37.469 --> 19:39.847
‐ You couldn't even give me one hour?!

19:39.847 --> 19:42.683
You turned an easy diplomatic solution

19:42.683 --> 19:45.644
into a slaughter out of sheer laziness!

19:45.644 --> 19:47.896
Is that what being a knight means to you?

19:47.896 --> 19:51.650
‐ Being a knight means killing first
and not thinking about it later.

19:51.650 --> 19:55.070
And if you throw an hourglass
at my head again,

19:55.070 --> 19:56.905
we're gonna have a problem, Sir Patrick.

19:56.905 --> 19:59.157
‐ Did you just call him <i>Sir</i> Patrick?

19:59.157 --> 20:00.742
‐ I knighted him, Daddy.

20:00.742 --> 20:02.786
‐ You can't knight people.

20:02.786 --> 20:05.414
That's ridiculous!
‐ Stop undercutting me

20:05.414 --> 20:07.165
in front of the fucking help!

20:07.165 --> 20:10.252
‐ Come on, Sir Styles,
let's go dig up that brothel.

20:10.252 --> 20:13.213
‐ I have <i>glass</i> in my <i>face</i>!

20:13.213 --> 20:14.923
‐ Pull it together.

20:14.923 --> 20:16.800
‐ So after all that,
I'm not even a knight?

20:16.800 --> 20:18.927
You know what?
That's fucking perfect

20:18.927 --> 20:21.763
because I am done!
I've had enough of this insane‐‐

20:21.763 --> 20:24.141
‐ Boop, boop, you're a knight.
Happy, sweetie?

20:24.141 --> 20:26.685
‐ No! I don't wanna be a knight!

20:26.685 --> 20:29.897
I quit! I resign! I'm out!

20:29.897 --> 20:33.192
‐ You can't quit being a knight.
The only way out is death.

20:33.192 --> 20:35.319
‐ But that's not for a <i>long</i> time.

20:35.319 --> 20:38.906
An adult male in this day and age
will live well into his late 20s.

20:41.074 --> 20:43.577
‐ Nobody panic.
That could be the pizza guy.

20:44.703 --> 20:47.706
♪

20:52.753 --> 20:55.589
‐ Well, <i>one</i> of those guys
has gotta be the pizza guy.

20:55.589 --> 20:57.090
There's, like, a <i>million</i> of them.

21:01.720 --> 21:04.014
‐ If they're here to help us
fight the mole people,

21:04.014 --> 21:05.766
they're gonna feel pretty stupid.

21:05.766 --> 21:08.894
‐ No, sire.
The mole people sank their castles

21:08.894 --> 21:11.146
because they couldn't tell
us surface people apart.

21:11.146 --> 21:13.690
Racist.
‐ That makes me the hero

21:13.690 --> 21:15.150
who defeated the mole people.

21:15.150 --> 21:17.653
‐ That makes <i>us</i> the kingdom that got rich

21:17.653 --> 21:20.364
while the mole people were
sinking the wrong people's shit.

21:20.364 --> 21:21.949
‐ Not a great spin.

21:21.949 --> 21:24.368
‐ King Rami's been looking
for an excuse to invade.

21:24.368 --> 21:28.330
Now, he has the other kings
on his side. We're fucked.

21:28.330 --> 21:30.791
‐ We? I think you mean you.

21:30.791 --> 21:34.336
Kings don't fight wars. Knights do.
Go get 'em, Sir Patrick.

21:36.088 --> 21:37.840
‐ Pizza for King Merriman.

21:37.840 --> 21:39.633
‐ Bless the baby Jesus!

21:39.633 --> 21:41.844
‐ I don't see any garlic knots.

21:41.844 --> 21:43.720
‐ Sorry. Rain check on the knots.

21:43.720 --> 21:46.223
Our knot guy's out with a rash.

21:46.223 --> 21:49.643
‐ Unacceptable!
Merriman, punish her at once.

21:49.643 --> 21:51.186
‐ Fine.

21:53.188 --> 21:54.857
Boop, boop, you're a knight. Mm!

21:54.857 --> 21:57.317
‐ Aw, man. I'm a knight now?

21:57.317 --> 22:00.112
I was <i>so</i> close to making manager.

22:00.112 --> 22:03.657
‐ Well, good luck down there,
Sir... Kylie.

22:03.657 --> 22:06.535
‐ Goddammit.

22:06.535 --> 22:09.538
♪

22:36.231 --> 22:39.234
♪

22:51.205 --> 22:53.081
CHILD:
<i>That was amazing.</i>
